<collectingRegion id="C216F87EFF83FFB673205035FA68D16A" box="[1341,1432,1322,1348]" country="Mexico" name="Oaxaca" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Oaxaca</collectingRegion>
. Three specimens were associated with oak (
<taxonomicName id="C7D24D1FFF83FFB674B1504CFCCAD142" box="[684,826,1362,1388]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="32A6EA8EFF83FFB674B1504CFCFED142" box="[684,782,1363,1388]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Quercus</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
) and several others were collected in “mesófilos”, mountain forests or cloud forests (label data).
</paragraph>
